cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper is about a video object detection method that uses attention mechanism and convolutional long short-term memory (ConvLSTM). The method is evaluated on ImageNet VID dataset and 2DMOT15 dataset, which are commonly used in computer vision and robotics research. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the method involves machine learning techniques such as attention mechanism and ConvLSTM, which are related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The evaluation on 2DMOT15 dataset also suggests that the method may be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and robotics (cs.RO) research.
